# Enrich — Certifications

Apply for certificate images, PDFs, Credly links, or CV cert sections.

Cross-check `projects.cache.json` entry `certificates` when enriching.

## Target file

`ai-agents/database/certifications.json` → `records[]`

## Record shape

```json
{
  "id": "cert-{issuer-slug}-{short-name}",
  "name": "AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate",
  "issuer": "AWS",
  "issuedAt": "2024-05",
  "expiresAt": null,
  "credentialId": null,
  "verifyUrl": null,
  "imagePath": "ai-agents/sources/certificates/aws-saa.png",
  "categories": ["cloud", "architecture"],
  "relatedRoles": ["devops", "backend"],
  "featured": false,
  "sourceIds": [],
  "confidence": "verified",
  "enrichment_status": "complete",
  "enriched_at": "...",
  "enriched_by": "cursor"
}
```

## Steps

1. Save certificate image to `ai-agents/sources/certificates/` if provided.
2. Dedupe by `name` + `issuer` — update dates/verifyUrl if renewed.
3. Set `featured: true` for home proof strip candidates (max 3–5 total across DB).

## Rules

- Read image/PDF to confirm exact cert name and date.
- Link to Certificates repo paths in `projects.cache.json` when same file exists there.
- Do not mark expired certs as current without user confirmation.
